Steven Sims Jr. (born March 31, 1997) is an American football wide receiver and return specialist for the Washington Redskins of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at the University of Kansas and signed with the Redskins as an undrafted free agent in 2019.


== Professional career ==
Sims signed with the Washington Redskins as an undrafted free agent on April 30, 2019. After having a strong camp performance, Sims made the final roster cuts on August 31, 2019, beating out fellow wide receivers, Cam Sims, Brian Quick, Jehu Chesson, and the Redskins' 2016 first rounder Josh Doctson. He had his first career reception, a three-yard gain from Case Keenum, in a week 2 loss to the Dallas Cowboys, along with three carries for sixteen yards. He had his first career touchdown, a 65-yard rushing touchdown, against the New England Patriots on October 6, 2019.


